      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk why you keep bringing up goblins lol. it's kinda distracting. anyway, lets just stick to the econ stuff. so if there is uncertainty in these estimates, does that change how the opportunity cost is viewed in a formal analysis? like how do they account for the risk of being wrong?",
